Class DeletedException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class DeletedException
extends java.lang.RuntimeException
    This exception is thrown when a Deletable object has an operation called on it that cannot be performed due to now deleted information and/or references.
    Author:
    Trent "Whirvis" Summerlin
